

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Us";
}

<style>
    .full-bleed {
        margin-left: calc(-50vw + 50%);
        margin-right: calc(-50vw + 50%);
    }
</style>

<!-- PAGE HEADER -->
<div class="full-bleed" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d0000 0%, #1a0000 60%, #0f0f0f 100%);">
    <div class="container py-5 text-center">
        <p class="text-warning text-uppercase fw-semibold small mb-2">Who We Are</p>
        <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold text-white mb-3">About Us</h1>
        <p class="text-white-50 mx-auto" style="max-width:560px;">
            Two friends, sharing their passion of movies.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- MEET THE AUTHORS -->
<div class="py-5">
    <div class="row g-5 align-items-center mb-5">
        <div class="col-lg-2 text-center">
            <div class="rounded-circle bg-dark border border-warning d-inline-flex align-items-center justify-content-center fw-bold text-warning"
                 style="width:100px;height:100px;font-size:2.5rem;">
                R
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-10">
            <p class="text-warning text-uppercase fw-semibold small mb-1">Co-Author</p>
            <h2 class="fw-bold text-white mb-2">Rahim</h2>
            <p class="text-white-50 lh-lg mb-3">
                I started watching movies while I was very young, and I quickly became fascinated by them to the point where I once thought I might become a film director myself, just to understand how stories are built frame by frame. Over time, that early curiosity settled into something simpler: I just really enjoy movies and the way they can pull you into different worlds for a couple of hours.
            </p>
            <div class="d-flex gap-3 flex-wrap">
                <span class="badge bg-dark border border-secondary text-secondary">Drama</span>
                <span class="badge bg-dark border border-secondary text-secondary">Sci-Fi</span>
                <span class="badge bg-dark border border-secondary text-secondary">Arthouse</span>
                <span class="badge bg-dark border border-secondary text-secondary">Thriller</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="border-secondary">

    <div class="row g-5 align-items-center mt-2">
        <div class="col-lg-2 text-center">
            <div class="rounded-circle bg-dark border border-warning d-inline-flex align-items-center justify-content-center fw-bold text-warning"
                 style="width:100px;height:100px;font-size:2.5rem;">
                K
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-10">
            <p class="text-warning text-uppercase fw-semibold small mb-1">Co-Author</p>
            <h2 class="fw-bold text-white mb-2">Kira</h2>
            <p class="text-white-50 lh-lg mb-3">
                Films have always been how I process the world. I love stories that sneak up on you —
                the ones that seem small and then hit you days later when you're washing dishes.
                My favourites tend to be character-driven dramas and anything with a stunning performance at the centre.
                On Cinema Diary I handle the emotional autopsies, the watchlist curation, and all the fun facts.
            </p>
            <div class="d-flex gap-3 flex-wrap">
                <span class="badge bg-dark border border-secondary text-secondary">Drama</span>
                <span class="badge bg-dark border border-secondary text-secondary">Romance</span>
                <span class="badge bg-dark border border-secondary text-secondary">Horror</span>
                <span class="badge bg-dark border border-secondary text-secondary">Animation</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- OUR STORY -->
<div class="full-bleed bg-black py-5">
    <div class="container py-2">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-8 text-center">
                <p class="text-warning text-uppercase fw-semibold small mb-2">Our Story</p>
                <h2 class="display-5 fw-bold text-white mb-4">How Cinema Diary Started</h2>
                <p class="text-white-50 lh-lg mb-3">
                    It started with a simple realization: people don’t really discuss movies the way they do with sports, where opinions, debates, and analysis are part of the experience. That gap felt like something worth addressing, so we decided to build a space where film thoughts could actually be shared and explored.
                </p>
                <p class="text-white-50 lh-lg mb-3">
                    Cinemary started as an idea we came up with while thinking about what we could build for our final project in an ASP.NET class. What began as a simple assignment quickly turned into something more meaningful — a space where we could combine our interest in web development with our shared love of movies.
                </p>
                <p class="text-white-50 lh-lg">
                    If even one person discovers a film they love because of something we wrote here,
                    that's everything we hoped for.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- WHAT WE BELIEVE -->
<div class="py-5">
    <div class="text-center mb-5">
        <p class="text-warning text-uppercase fw-semibold small mb-1">Our Values</p>
        <h2 class="display-5 fw-bold text-white mb-2">What We Believe</h2>
        <hr class="border-warning opacity-100 mx-auto" style="width:48px;border-width:3px;">
    </div>

    <div class="row g-4">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card bg-dark border-secondary h-100 p-4 text-center text-white">
                <div class="fs-1 mb-3">🎯</div>
                <h5 class="fw-bold text-warning mb-2">Honesty Over Hype</h5>
                <p class="text-white-50 small mb-0">
                    We call it as we see it. If a film disappointed us, we'll say so — respectfully,
                    but clearly. No hype cycles, no bandwagon reviewing.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card bg-dark border-secondary h-100 p-4 text-center text-white">
                <div class="fs-1 mb-3">🌍</div>
                <h5 class="fw-bold text-warning mb-2">Cinema Without Borders</h5>
                <p class="text-white-50 small mb-0">
                    Great films come from everywhere. We watch across languages, countries, and genres —
                    and we want this diary to reflect that breadth.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card bg-dark border-secondary h-100 p-4 text-center text-white">
                <div class="fs-1 mb-3">💬</div>
                <h5 class="fw-bold text-warning mb-2">Film is Conversation</h5>
                <p class="text-white-50 small mb-0">
                    Cinema is most alive when people talk about it. That's what this diary is —
                    an ongoing conversation between two friends, and anyone else who wants to join.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- CTA -->
<div class="full-bleed bg-black py-5 mb-0">
    <div class="container py-2 text-center">
        <h3 class="fw-bold text-white mb-3">Start Exploring</h3>
        <p class="text-white-50 mb-4">Browse our picks, read our thoughts, or discover something new.</p>
        <div class="d-flex gap-3 justify-content-center flex-wrap">
            <a asp-controller="Movie" asp-action="TopPicks" class="btn btn-warning fw-semibold text-dark px-4">Top Picks</a>
            <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="MovieThoughts" class="btn btn-outline-warning px-4">Movie Thoughts</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

